INDEX TO MARRIAGES recorded in the Counties of Maryland Il, = 1930 based on copies filed by the County Clerks of the Circuit Court with the State Department of Health MARYLAND STATE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH Bureau of Vital Statistics in cooperation with WPA projects #7071 and #7114 1941 Expl tion of Form Used The surnames of the grooms are filed by the Russell-Soundex system, arranged by given names in alphabetical order within each Soundex group. The complete given name is spelled out when given on the cer- tificate, and where space permits, otherwise abbreviations and in- itials are used. The ages of groom and bride are shown in the second and sixth columns, respectively. The color, or race, of the groom is shown by a one-letter abbreviation in the third column; the color of the bride is ordinarily the same. If the color of the bride differs from that of the groom, this is shown by the letter in parentheses following the bride's name. The birthplaces of groom and bride are designated by two-letter ab- previations in the fourth and seventh columns, respectively. The eighth, ninth, and tenth columns give the month, day, and year when the ceremony was performed. The last column shows the county in which the license was issued. Abbreviations for color, and for geographical units used, are listed on the following page. E ion of Used - A dash is used if the item was omitted on the certificate. ? <A question mark in the age column means that the age was given as "over 21", d+ A number sign in the left margin indicates that the certificate was filed out of order. * When the date of the ceremony was not shown on the certificate, the date the license was issued is used instead, and an asterisk ig typed above the comma in the date. x If the license was returned marked "not used", a small x is typed in the left margin, and the date of issuance of the license is used. o A gmall o in the left margin indicates that the name is spelled erroneously, and will be found retyped correctly under another Soundex number. reviati for r W White C Colored (Negro) Y Yellow (Japanese, Chinese) B Brown (Filipino) I Indian re i for C i as County where license was issued Place of birth Counties of State or Maryland Country Allegany Alleg Alleg 01 Alabama Al Nevada Nv Anne Arundel An Ar An Ar 02 Arizona Ag New Hampshire NH Baltimore Balto Balto 03 Arkansas Ak New Jersey NJ Calvert Calvt Calvt 04 California Ca New Mexico NM Caroline Carlin Carlin 05 Colorado Co New York NY Carroll Carrl Carrl 06 Connecticut Cn North Carolina NC Cecil Cecil Decil 07 Delaware De North Dakota ND Charles Chas Chas 08 Distr. of Col.
